## Milestone 1 RESULT ‚ÄĒ poison enumeration complete (definitive surface)

Poisoned the 3 read-path `FILE*` fields (`PoisonPgenFile*`) and compiled
`pgenlib_read.cc` in isolation with the CMake pgenlib flags. **34 error sites, all
in `pgenlib_read.cc`** (nothing else in the compiled read path touches these
fields ‚ÄĒ completeness confirmed by the compiler, not just search). The full op
vocabulary is just **5 operations**:

| op | sites | notes |
|---|---|---|
| open (`fopen` + assign an open `FILE*` into the field) | 3 | L2067 `pgrp->ff = fopen(...)`, L709/825 assign a local into `shared_ff`/`pgi_ff` |
| `fseeko` | 9 | seek to a variant record offset |
| `ftello` | 2 | position query |
| `fread_unlocked` | 2 | the byte pull (macro ‚Üí `fread`) |
| `fclose_null(&field)` | 5 | pgenlib helper, takes `FILE**` (close + null) |
| *(read field into a local `FILE*`)* | 3 | e.g. `FILE* header_ff = pgfip->pgi_ff;` ‚ÄĒ the local + its uses convert too |

`getc_unlocked` / `rewind` do **not** touch these fields (they operate on the
in-memory block buffer, not the file). So the shim needs exactly:
`open / seek / tell / read / close_null` ‚ÄĒ five thin wrappers over a tagged
`PgenFile { FILE* ff; void* rhandle; uint64_t roff; }`; local branch = the libc
call unchanged (zero hot-path diff), remote branch = a positioned read.

### Seam design ‚ÄĒ resolved via DuckDB's VFS + a local fastpath

The context problem (remote open needs the query `ClientContext` for httpfs
credentials/secrets, `file_search_path`, settings) is solved by **opening the
`.pgen` through DuckDB's VFS extension-side**, and keeping raw `fopen` as a
local fastpath. Confirmed API: `FileSystem::OpenFile(path, READ, opener)`
(file_system.hpp:149) + `ClientContextFileOpener(context)` whose opener carries
`SecretManager` (file_opener.hpp:45) ‚Üí httpfs credentials/settings. Once open, the
`FileHandle` is **self-contained** ‚ÄĒ positioned `Read(buf, n, location)` needs no
further context.

**So the seam pgenlib needs is only `pread / fsize / close`** ‚ÄĒ *no `open`
callback, no context, no DuckDB types in pgenlib.* The extension opens the handle
(it has the context) and hands it in.

**Local default fastpath (necessary, not just nice):** `FileHandle::Read(...,
location)` does one `pread` **syscall per call, no stdio readahead**, while pgenlib
does ~1 read per variant record ‚Üí a local sequential scan would regress to
syscall-per-record vs stdio `fread`'s buffered reads. So:

- **plain-local** (`FileSystem::IsRemoteFile` false / `FileHandle::OnDiskFile`) ‚Üí
  keep raw `fopen` / `fread_unlocked` (buffered, zero change to today's hot path).
- **remote / VFS-resolved** ‚Üí `FileHandle` positioned reads, buffering from
  `cache_httpfs` (or our block layer).

`PgenFile { FILE* ff; void* vfs_handle; uint64_t vfs_off; }`; the 5 op wrappers
branch on `vfs_handle != nullptr`. The extension picks the branch at open with
`IsRemoteFile`/`OnDiskFile`.

**Bonus folded in (bigger than S3):** routing `.pgen` through the VFS makes
`file_search_path`, `pathmacro:`, glob, and every DuckDB protocol work for `.pgen`
**uniformly** ‚ÄĒ closing the long-standing "`.pgen` bypasses the VFS" gap
([[pathmacro-readpfile-integration]]) for free, not just enabling S3. A previously
separate limitation becomes a side effect of this work.

## Known surface (superseded by the milestone-1 result above)

- **State**: 3 `FILE*` fields (above).
- **Ops**: `fopen`, `fseeko`, `ftello`, `fread_unlocked` (macro‚Üí`fread`),
  `getc_unlocked`, `rewind`, `fclose` ‚ÄĒ concentrated in `pgenlib_read.cc`.
- **Helpers that take `FILE*`**: `fread_checked` (and friends) in `plink2_base.h` ‚ÄĒ
  these are part of the fixpoint, not just the 3 fields.
- **Access pattern**: coarse seek+read per variant record (‚Čą1:1 `fseeko`:`fread`).

## Patch mechanism (defer heavy wiring until milestone 3 is green)

- Edits live as **re-appliable patches** to the `third_party/plink-ng` submodule
  (git-format-patch under `patches/plink-ng/`), applied idempotently at build time.
  Precedent for build-time injection: `src/musl_compat.h` force-included via CMake.
- Must be idempotent (re-apply = no-op; a `git submodule update` after a bump
  doesn't fight it) and CI-reproducible from a clean checkout.
- Structured minimal + one-logical-change-per-patch so they are **upstreamable**
  (the `plink2_text.h:137` "network support later" comment is the open door).
- The drift canary (`scripts/check_vendored_drift.sh`) treats the patch as the
  intended delta and verifies the rest is unchanged.

